Class EventDetails

androidx.fragment.app.Fragment
com.example.cmput301w24t33.organizerFragments.EventDetails
All Implemented Interfaces:
android.content.ComponentCallbacks, android.view.View.OnCreateContextMenuListener, androidx.activity.result.ActivityResultCaller, androidx.lifecycle.HasDefaultViewModelProviderFactory, androidx.lifecycle.LifecycleOwner, androidx.lifecycle.ViewModelStoreOwner, androidx.savedstate.SavedStateRegistryOwner, ShareQRFragment.ShareQRDialogListener, Serializable
public class EventDetails extends androidx.fragment.app.Fragment implements ShareQRFragment.ShareQRDialogListener, Serializable
A fragment class to display the details of an event within the application. It allows the organizer to view event details and provides navigation to edit the event, manage attendees, and send notifications.
